com.baypackets.ase.sbb
Interface MsOperationResult

public interface MsOperationResult

The MsOperationResult interface defines an object that encapsulates the results of an RTP interaction between a media server and network endpoint. These results can include the digits collected from the endpoint's TUI, the user's voice recording, and more, depending on the type of interaction that was initiated.

Author:
BayPackets
See Also:
MsSessionController

Field Detail

PLAY_DURATION

public static final java.lang.String PLAY_DURATION
This attribute can be used to get the duration of the message played in milliseconds. The attribute will return a String value of the duration.

COLLECTED_DIGITS

public static final java.lang.String COLLECTED_DIGITS
This string is passed to the "getAttribute" method to return a String containing the digits that were collected by the media server during the RTP interaction with the network endpoint. If the interaction did not involve a digit collection, the method returns NULL.

RECORDING_LENGTH

public static final java.lang.String RECORDING_LENGTH
This string is passed to the "getAttribute" method to return a String value indicating the length in milliseconds of the voice recording taken by the media server during the RTP interaction with the network endpoint. If the interaction did not involve a voice recording, the method returns NULL.

STATUS_NO_DIGIT_MATCH

public static final java.lang.String STATUS_NO_DIGIT_MATCH
This value is returned by the "getStatus()" method to indicate that the digits entered by the user during a play/collect operation did not match the pattern specified in the request.

STATUS_NO_DIGIT_INPUT

public static final java.lang.String STATUS_NO_DIGIT_INPUT
This value is returned by the "getStatus()" method to indicate that no digits were entered by the user in the time period specified in the play/collect request.

STATUS_TIMED_OUT

public static final java.lang.String STATUS_TIMED_OUT
This value is returned by the "getStatus()" method to indicate that the play/collect operation timed out.

STATUS_SUCCESS

public static final java.lang.String STATUS_SUCCESS
This value is returned by the "getStatus()" method to indicate that the media server interaction completed as specified in the operation request.

Method Detail

isSuccessfull

public boolean isSuccessfull()
This method returns a boolean value specifying if the RTP interaction initiated between the media server and network endpoint was completed succesfully.

Returns:
True if the interaction was successful or False otherwise.

getStatus

public java.lang.String getStatus()
This method returns a value indicating the result status of a media server operation. The possible return values are specified by the following public static constants defined in this interface:
  • STATUS_NO_DIGIT_MATCH
  • STATUS_NO_DIGIT_INPUT
  • STATUS_TIMED_OUT
  • STATUS_SUCCESS

getAttribute

public java.lang.Object getAttribute(java.lang.String name)
This method returns the specified result attribute of the RTP interaction between the media server and network endpoint.

Parameters:
name - - The name of the result attribute to return.
Returns:
The specified attribute value or null if no such attribute was contained in the result.

getAttributeNames

public java.util.Iterator getAttributeNames()
This method returns the attribute names supported by the type of RTP interaction that occurred. For example, if the interaction resulted in both a voice recording and digit collection, the following values would be present in the array returned by this method: RECORDING_URL, RECORDING_LENGTH, COLLECTED_DIGITS.

Returns:
The names of the attributes contained by this object or an empty array if none are present.

getActiveSpeakerList

public java.util.Iterator getActiveSpeakerList()
This method returns an iterator containing the Connection IDs of all the currently active speakers in a conference. If this result does not contain the active speaker notification, this method would return an empty iterator.

Returns:
The Connection Identifier for each active speaker in the conference.

getResponseCode

public java.lang.String getResponseCode()
This method returns the response code(if any) associated with a media server operation

Returns:
The response code of the media server operation.
